.SH NAME
Bitcoin::Crypto::Exception \- Exception classes for Bitcoin::Crypto
.SH SYNOPSIS
.IX Header "SYNOPSIS"
.Vb 6
\&        try {
\&                decode_segwit(\*(AqNot a segwit address\*(Aq);
\&        }
\&        catch ($error) {
\&                # $error is an instance of Bitcoin::Crypto::Exception and stringifies automatically
\&                warn "$error";
\&
\&                # it also contains some information about the problem to avoid regex matching
\&                if ($error\->isa(\*(AqBitcoin::Crypto::Exception::Bech32InputFormat\*(Aq)) {
\&                        log $error\->message;
\&                }
\&        }
.Ve
.SH DESCRIPTION
.IX Header "DESCRIPTION"
An exception wrapper class with automatic stringification and standardized
raising.
.PP
Contains inline packages that identify parts that went wrong (like
\&\f(CW\*(C`Bitcoin::Crypto::Exception::Sign\*(C'\fR for errors in signature generation). Search
individual Bitcoin::Crypto packages documentation for a list the exception
classes to check for extra control flow when needed.
.SH "EXCEPTION SUBCLASSES"
.IX Header "EXCEPTION SUBCLASSES"
This module defines the following subclasses to Bitcoin::Crypto::Exception:
.SS Bitcoin::Crypto::Exception::Transaction
.IX Subsection "Bitcoin::Crypto::Exception::Transaction"
Thrown when a general problem with a transaction is detected, for example:
non\-script verification failure, corrupted serialized transaction data.
.SS Bitcoin::Crypto::Exception::UTXO
.IX Subsection "Bitcoin::Crypto::Exception::UTXO"
Thrown when a problem with UTXO is detected, most notably inability to find the UTXO.
.SS Bitcoin::Crypto::Exception::Sign
.IX Subsection "Bitcoin::Crypto::Exception::Sign"
Thrown when a problem occurs during signing a transaction or message.
.SS Bitcoin::Crypto::Exception::KeyCreate
.IX Subsection "Bitcoin::Crypto::Exception::KeyCreate"
Thrown when a problem occurs during creation of a key.
.SS Bitcoin::Crypto::Exception::KeyDerive
.IX Subsection "Bitcoin::Crypto::Exception::KeyDerive"
Thrown when a problem occurs during derivation of a key.
.SS Bitcoin::Crypto::Exception::MnemonicCheck
.IX Subsection "Bitcoin::Crypto::Exception::MnemonicCheck"
Thrown when a mnemonic checking was unsuccessful.
.SS Bitcoin::Crypto::Exception::Base58
.IX Subsection "Bitcoin::Crypto::Exception::Base58"
Thrown when a general base58 format problem is detected.
.SS Bitcoin::Crypto::Exception::Base58InputFormat
.IX Subsection "Bitcoin::Crypto::Exception::Base58InputFormat"
Thrown when input does not look like valid base58. Subclass of
"Bitcoin::Crypto::Exception::Base58".
.SS Bitcoin::Crypto::Exception::Base58InputChecksum
.IX Subsection "Bitcoin::Crypto::Exception::Base58InputChecksum"
Thrown when base58check input checksum is invalid. Subclass of
"Bitcoin::Crypto::Exception::Base58".
.SS Bitcoin::Crypto::Exception::Bech32
.IX Subsection "Bitcoin::Crypto::Exception::Bech32"
Thrown when a general Bech32 format problem is detected.
.SS Bitcoin::Crypto::Exception::Bech32InputFormat
.IX Subsection "Bitcoin::Crypto::Exception::Bech32InputFormat"
Thrown when input does not look like valid bech32. Subclass of
"Bitcoin::Crypto::Exception::Bech32".
.SS Bitcoin::Crypto::Exception::Bech32InputData
.IX Subsection "Bitcoin::Crypto::Exception::Bech32InputData"
Thrown when input is valid bech32, but contains invalid data. Subclass of
"Bitcoin::Crypto::Exception::Bech32".
.SS Bitcoin::Crypto::Exception::Bech32InputChecksum
.IX Subsection "Bitcoin::Crypto::Exception::Bech32InputChecksum"
Thrown when bech32 input checksum is invalid. Subclass of
"Bitcoin::Crypto::Exception::Bech32".
.SS Bitcoin::Crypto::Exception::SegwitProgram
.IX Subsection "Bitcoin::Crypto::Exception::SegwitProgram"
Thrown when an issue with Segregated Witness program is detected.
.SS Bitcoin::Crypto::Exception::ScriptType
.IX Subsection "Bitcoin::Crypto::Exception::ScriptType"
Thrown when an unexpected script type is encountered.
.SS Bitcoin::Crypto::Exception::ScriptOpcode
.IX Subsection "Bitcoin::Crypto::Exception::ScriptOpcode"
Thrown when unexpected script operation is encountered.
.SS Bitcoin::Crypto::Exception::ScriptPush
.IX Subsection "Bitcoin::Crypto::Exception::ScriptPush"
Thrown when bad script push operation is performed.
.SS Bitcoin::Crypto::Exception::Block
.IX Subsection "Bitcoin::Crypto::Exception::Block"
Thrown when a general problem with a block is detected.
.SS Bitcoin::Crypto::Exception::ScriptTree
.IX Subsection "Bitcoin::Crypto::Exception::ScriptTree"
Thrown when a general problem with a script tree is detected.
.SS Bitcoin::Crypto::Exception::ScriptCompilation
.IX Subsection "Bitcoin::Crypto::Exception::ScriptCompilation"
Thrown when a script compilation fails. It can only be thrown just
before the script is executed.
.SS Bitcoin::Crypto::Exception::ScriptRuntime
.IX Subsection "Bitcoin::Crypto::Exception::ScriptRuntime"
Thrown when an error occurs during script runtime.
.SS Bitcoin::Crypto::Exception::TransactionScript
.IX Subsection "Bitcoin::Crypto::Exception::TransactionScript"
Thrown when an error occurs in execution of scripts during
transaction validation. Subclass of
"Bitcoin::Crypto::Exception::Transaction" and
"Bitcoin::Crypto::Exception::ScriptRuntime".
.SS Bitcoin::Crypto::Exception::NetworkCheck
.IX Subsection "Bitcoin::Crypto::Exception::NetworkCheck"
Thrown when an assumption about network is not met. This can happen
in single\-network mode or if a network parameter is used, but it
does not match the arguments.
.SS Bitcoin::Crypto::Exception::NetworkConfig
.IX Subsection "Bitcoin::Crypto::Exception::NetworkConfig"
Thrown when network configuration is bad or insufficient to perform
the operation.
.SS Bitcoin::Crypto::Exception::Address
.IX Subsection "Bitcoin::Crypto::Exception::Address"
Thrown when a general error connected to addresses is encountered.
.SS Bitcoin::Crypto::Exception::AddressGenerate
.IX Subsection "Bitcoin::Crypto::Exception::AddressGenerate"
Thrown when an error is encountered while generating an address. Subclass of
"Bitcoin::Crypto::Exception::Address".
.SS Bitcoin::Crypto::Exception::PSBT
.IX Subsection "Bitcoin::Crypto::Exception::PSBT"
Thrown when a problem with PSBT format was encountered.
.SH INTERFACE
.IX Header "INTERFACE"
.SS Attributes
.IX Subsection "Attributes"
\fImessage\fR
.IX Subsection "message"
.PP
The wrapped error message (a string). Note: this is the raw message,
not the serialized form like in "as_string".
.PP
\fIcaller\fR
.IX Subsection "caller"
.PP
\&\fBNot assignable in the constructor\fR
.PP
An array ref containing: package name, file name and line number (same
as \f(CW\*(C`[caller()]\*(C'\fR perl expression). It will point to the first place from
outside Bitcoin::Crypto which called it. May be undefined if it cannot find a
calling source.
.SS Methods
.IX Subsection "Methods"
\fInew\fR
.IX Subsection "new"
.PP
.Vb 1
\&        $runner = Bitcoin::Crypto::Exception\->new(%data)
.Ve
.PP
This is a standard Moo constructor, which can be used to create the object. It
takes arguments specified in "Attributes". For exceptions, it\*(Aqs probably
better to use "raise" instead.
.PP
Returns class instance.
.PP
\fIas_string\fR
.IX Subsection "as_string"
.PP
.Vb 1
\&        $error_info = $object\->as_string()
.Ve
.PP
Stringifies the error, using the "message" method, "caller" method and some
extra text for context.
.PP
\fIraise\fR
.IX Subsection "raise"
.PP
.Vb 2
\&        $object\->raise()
\&        $class\->raise($message)
.Ve
.PP
Creates a new instance and throws it. If used on an object, throws it right away.
.PP
.Vb 8
\&        try {
\&                # throws, but will be catched
\&                Bitcoin::Crypto::Exception\->raise(\*(Aqsomething went wrong\*(Aq);
\&        }
\&        catch ($exception) {
\&                # throws again
\&                $exception\->raise;
\&        }
.Ve
.PP
\fIthrow\fR
.IX Subsection "throw"
.PP
An alias to \f(CW\*(C`raise\*(C'\fR.
.PP
\fItrap_into\fR
.IX Subsection "trap_into"
.PP
.Vb 1
\&        $sub_result = $class\->trap_into($sub, $prefix)
.Ve
.PP
Executes the given subroutine in an exception\-trapping environment. Any
exceptions thrown inside the subroutine \f(CW$sub\fR will be re\-thrown after turning
them into objects of the given \f(CW\*(C`::Exception\*(C'\fR class. If no exception is thrown,
method returns the value returned by \f(CW$sub\fR.
.PP
.Vb 3
\&        my $result = Bitcoin::Crypto::Exception\->trap_into(sub {
\&                die \*(Aqsomething went wrong\*(Aq;
\&        });
.Ve
.PP
\&\f(CW$prefix\fR can be specified to better format the message.
